{
  "texts": [
    "In this context, one of the most promising approaches is adopted by the BBMRI-ERIC infrastructure.",
    "The concept of MIABIS was introduced in 2012 by the Sweden BBMRI to facilitate sample collection and data sharing.",
    "Subsequently, it was further updated in 2016, upgrading the components defining biobanks, collections, and studies on an aggregated level [86].",
    "The integrated data can then be used for retrieving data in queries in a structured and organized form.",
    "The MIABIS Core version 2.0 is currently used in different biobank registers and catalogs, that is, in the BBMRI-ERIC Directory; the development and the improvement of MIABIS is currently coordinated by the Common Service IT operations of BBMRI-ERIC [87]."
  ]
}